OL,7,FBaroness Grey-Thompson said: "Disabled
OL,8,Fpeople have a legal right to turn up
OL,9,Fand go. So I had booked assistance,
OL,10,Fbut I hadn't made that train, so
OL,11,Flegally, I am allowed to turn up and
OL,12,Fask to get on a train.
OL,14,F"So my view is, once somebody has put
OL,15,Fme on a train, I have a contract,
OL,16,Fwhich means somebody should meet me at
OL,17,Fthe other end.
OL,26,@oD@^OUvD@AOU
